cs.FL, cs.DM, cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with automata theory and formal languages, which are typically classified under cs.FL. The use of monoids as memory suggests a connection to algebraic automata theory, which falls under cs.DM. The paper also discusses semi-linear full trios, which are a topic in logic and algebra, and may be classified under cs.LO. The investigation of valence pushdown automata and their relationship to valence automata suggests a connection to graph theory and combinatorics, which may be classified under cs.GT. Finally, the paper discusses context-free valence grammars, which may be classified under cs.IT (information theory).
